<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="508" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/113.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister to the Dominican
                                    Republic</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 8, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>[After repeating the telegram from Mr. Furniss, dated June 6, the
                            telegram continues:]</p>
                        <p>If this is true, you will at once impress upon the Dominican Government
                            the necessity for refraining from any such action.</p>
                        <pb facs="0465" n="349" xml:id="pg_349"/>
                        <p>The boundary dispute negotiations have been held up for more than a month
                            by Peynado’s delay in presenting a memorandum promised to the Department
                            regarding encroachments by Haiti on Dominican territory.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>